
Task 1 – Create a New User

Open Microsoft Entra admin center
 and log in.

Navigate: Users → All users → + New user → Create new user.

Enter user details:

User principal name: test

Display name: test

First name: test

Last name: test

Account enabled: Checked

Usage location: Australia

Copy the auto-generated password.

Click Review + create → Create.

Subtask – Login to confirm user

Open an InPrivate window, log in with new user credentials, complete MFA setup if prompted.

Screenshot:
![Task 1 Screenshot](screenshots/task1.png)

Task 2 – Add a License

Open Microsoft 365 admin center
 and log in.

Navigate: Billing → Licenses → Microsoft Power Automate Free → + Assign licenses.

Select user Bhogeswar and click Assign.

Screenshot:
![Task 2 Screenshot](screenshots/task2.png)

Task 3 – Invite an External User

In Entra admin center: Users → All users → + New user → Invite external user.

Enter details:

Email: ExtUser@testemail.com

Display name: External User

Message: Thank you for joining the company for this short work project.

Click Review + Create → Create.

Screenshot:
![Task 3 Screenshot](screenshots/task3.png)

Task 4 – Assign a Role to a User

In Entra admin center: Users → All users → Bhogeswar Kalita → Assigned roles → + Add assignment.

Assign role: Attribute Definition Reader, Assignment type: Eligible.

Alternate method

Navigate: Roles & admins → Attribute Log Reader → + Add assignment → Select Bhogeswar Kalita → Active → Enter justification → Assign.

Screenshot:
![Task 4 Screenshot](screenshots/task4.png)

Task 5 – Bulk Import Users

In Entra admin center: Users → All users → Bulk operations → Bulk create → Download template.

Edit CSV with your domain and user info.

Upload CSV in Step 3 of Bulk create and click Submit.

Verify that the users were created.

Screenshot:
![Task 5 Screenshot](screenshots/task5.png)
